40|$|The <b>Sieverts</b> {{technique}} {{is commonly used}} for determining gas uptake, particularly for hydrogen storage material characterisation. Despite a considerable literature on correct technique, best practice and sources of potential errors, there is still confusion concerning application of this technique. We address three aspects of the <b>Sieverts</b> technique, (thermal transpiration, volume calibration {{and the effect of}} valve volume) {{in the context of a}} recent publication. No Full Tex...|$|R
